## v1.2.0 (2026-05-09)

**Changed by:** ProjectOdyssey Phase G EASY-tier consolidation (PR #5363, 8-agent swarm contamination)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed

- Added new Phase 0a "Worktree-Isolation Branch-Namespace Contamination — When Parallel
  Dispatch BREAKS" documenting that `Task isolation=worktree` does NOT isolate the parent
  repo's git index/HEAD when N agents target N distinct branches
- Added decision matrix for when to serialize vs dispatch parallel
- Added cherry-pick consolidation recovery workflow (the PR #5363 fix)
- Added per-agent-brief branch-namespace check (`rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD` before commit)
- Added 2 Failed Attempts rows: 8-EASY-tier-branch swarm contamination (#5363); parallel
  Mnemosyne `/learn` amendments contamination
- Added Verified On row for ProjectOdyssey #5363
- Bumped to 1.2.0 (minor — new section, new failures, no breaking changes)
- Description trigger list extended from 5 to 8 conditions

### Why

`Task isolation=worktree` was assumed to provide complete isolation, but PR #5363 demonstrated
that path-level isolation does NOT prevent index/HEAD contention across N agents on N distinct
branches sharing a parent `.git/`. The fix is to either serialize EASY-tier batches OR
consolidate via cherry-pick into a single branch and close the individual worker PRs. Same
pattern recurs in Mnemosyne `/learn` parallel invocations on the shared agent-brain clone.

